  "text": ", and S 0 = R 0 , S 1 = R 1 , S 2 = ). By using Magma [CITATION_1] , we find that when p = 37, q = p 3 , and N = 4p 1 = 28, the index sets We have q = 37 3 = 107 2 + 4 \u00b7 99 2 = 37 2 + 4 \u00b7 111 2 . By Ma and Wang's results [CITATION_2] , the putative skew-symmetric fission scheme with 4 classes of a conference graph exists only if q \u2261 5 (mod 8) and there exist integers g, h such that q = g 2 + 4h 2 with g \u2261 1 (mod 4). Moreover, the first eigenmatrix P is of the form (\u22121 \u2212 \u221a q + \u22122q \u2212 2g \u221a q). It turns out that our example happens with g = 37. For the corresponding cyclotomic scheme of order 4 over F 37 3 , we have g = \u2212107.",
